# 🌐 Personal Portfolio Website

A modern and fully responsive **portfolio website** showcasing my skills, projects, and design aesthetics. Built using **HTML5**, **CSS3**, and **JavaScript**, with advanced effects powered by **Locomotive Scroll** and **Spline 3D**.

---

## 📌 Overview

This is my personal portfolio site designed to:

- Introduce who I am  
- Highlight my featured projects  
- Provide ways to contact me  
- Deliver a visually engaging and interactive user experience  

---

## ✨ Features

- ⚡ Smooth scrolling using **Locomotive Scroll**  
- 🎮 Interactive 3D objects using **Spline 3D**  
- 💻 Fully **responsive design** – adapts to all screen sizes  
- 💡 Clean UI/UX focused on performance and minimalism  
- 🧠 Well-structured sections:  
  - **About**  
  - **Projects**  
  - **Skills**  
  - **Contact**  
- 🎨 Custom fonts and icons for a unique look  

---

## 📁 Project Structure
├── index.html # Main HTML file
├── style.css # All styling and layout rules
├── script.js # Scroll, animation and interactivity logic
├── images/ # All image assets used in the site
├── about/ # Details about me, contact form, skill details
├── fonts/ # Custom font files
├── cards/ # Responsive component assets
├── projects/ # Project previews and details
├── readme/ # Previous version(s) of README if any


---

## 📌 Technologies Used

- **HTML5**
- **CSS3** with media queries
- **Vanilla JavaScript**
- **Locomotive Scroll** – [GitHub](https://github.com/locomotivemtl/locomotive-scroll)
- **Spline 3D** – [https://spline.design](https://spline.design)

---

## 📱 Responsive Design

The website adapts to:

- 📱 Mobile Devices  
- 💻 Tablets  
- 🖥️ Desktop Screens  

All components are optimized using modern CSS practices, flexible grid systems, and media queries.

---

## 🧠 Learnings & Goals

- Building custom animations  
- Implementing smooth scroll and 3D graphics  
- Practicing modular and responsive design  
- Preparing for real-world personal branding  

